      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly, here's a draft for your \"How to Request Time Off\" section:\n\n\n*How to Request Time Off*\n\nTo request time off, please follow these steps: \n\n1. Access your company's time management system and navigate to the \"Request Time Off\" page.\n2. Enter your personal details, including your name, email, and employee ID, in the appropriate fields.\n3. Select the start and end dates for your time off and ensure they do not conflict with company schedules or deadlines.\n4. Provide a brief reason for your request to assist managers in accommodating your absence.\n5. Confirm your request by reviewing all entered information, then save your changes.\n6. Email your direct supervisor a copy of the approved time off request, attaching any relevant documentation like vacation certificates.\n7. Follow up with your supervisor, usually within 24 hours, to confirm the received approval and to address any potential coverage questions.\n\n\nThis version includes multiple action verbs to ensure an \"action-oriented\" feel, as per your automated scoring system's requirement, while maintaining a clear, unambiguous instruction set for onboarding staff.",
